---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — StudentFlow"
  description="What StudentFlow collects, what it doesn't, and how to reach us. No tracking, no analytics, no ads."
>
  <article class="post">
    <a class="back" href="/">← Back to StudentFlow</a>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="date">Effective June 5, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No tracking. No analytics. No ads.</li>
        <li>Your study data (courses, assignments, grades, sessions) lives on your device.</li>
        <li>Sign in with Apple is optional. We only see what Apple gives us to identify your account.</li>
        <li>Tips go through Apple. We never see your payment info.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        StudentFlow is an iOS app and companion web sign-in at
        <a href="https://studentflowapp.com">studentflowapp.com</a>, made by
        Joey Maglalang. For any privacy question, email
        <a href="mailto:joeymaglalang91@gmail.com">joeymaglalang91@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect, and why</h2>

      <h3>1. Apple sign-in (optional)</h3>
      <p>
        If you choose to sign in with your Apple ID, Apple gives StudentFlow a
        stable user identifier and — on your first sign-in only — the name and
        email you choose to share. (That email can be Apple's private relay
        address; we can't see your real one if you pick that option.)
      </p>
      <p>
        That identifier is stored in our authentication backend
        (<a href="https://supabase.com">Supabase</a>) so the same account works
        in the app and on the web. We use it only to keep you signed in. We do
        not currently sync any study data to our servers — sign-in is
        identity-only.
      </p>

      <h3>2. Canvas calendar feed (you provide)</h3>
      <p>
        If you connect Canvas, you paste your personal Canvas calendar (ICS)
        URL into StudentFlow. That URL is stored on your device only.
        StudentFlow fetches the feed directly from Canvas to display your
        events — the URL never reaches our servers.
      </p>

      <h3>3. Claude API key (you provide)</h3>
      <p>
        AI features are coming soon. If you enter a Claude API key for them,
        it is stored on your device only. When AI features ship, requests will
        go directly from your device to Anthropic's API — we don't see your
        key or your prompts.
      </p>

      <h3>4. Tips (StoreKit)</h3>
      <p>
        Tips are processed entirely by Apple via StoreKit. StudentFlow receives
        a transaction receipt — never your name, billing address, or payment
        details.
      </p>

      <h3>5. Crash reports</h3>
      <p>
        If you have "Share with App Developers" enabled in your iOS Privacy &
        Security settings, Apple may share anonymized crash reports with us
        through App Store Connect. These reports contain no personal
        information.
      </p>

      <h2>What we don't collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not track you across other apps or websites.</li>
        <li>We do not collect analytics, advertising IDs, or usage metrics.</li>
        <li>We do not access your contacts, photos, microphone, camera, or location.</li>
        <li>We do not sell any data — there is no data to sell.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Where your data lives</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>On your device.</strong> Courses, assignments, GPA, timer
          sessions, settings, your Canvas URL, and your Claude key all live in
          iOS-managed storage on your device.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Supabase (sign-in only).</strong> The Apple-provided
          identifier and email associated with your StudentFlow account live
          in our Supabase project, used only to keep you signed in.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Apple.</strong> Transaction receipts for tips are handled by
          Apple under their own privacy policy.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You can use StudentFlow without signing in. Sign-in is optional.</li>
        <li>
          To delete your StudentFlow account (and the identity record we hold
          in Supabase), email
          <a href="mailto:joeymaglalang91@gmail.com">joeymaglalang91@gmail.com</a>
          and we'll remove it within 30 days.
        </li>
        <li>To remove study data from your device, uninstall the app.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        StudentFlow is not directed at children under 13. If you are under 13,
        please don't create an account.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        If we make material changes to this policy, we'll update the date at
        the top and — if you have an account — note it on your next sign-in.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:joeymaglalang91@gmail.com">joeymaglalang91@gmail.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
